title: Velaikaran
subTitle: Ragupathy, who lives with his grandfather in a village, goes to the city to find a job. Soon, he learns that his mother is living with a man named Rajkumar and decides to protect him from his enemies.

title: Arasatchi
subTitle: Siddharth, a young man, targets corrupt lawyers, especially those who defend criminals and bad guys. His next target is a lawyer from New Delhi who defends a rapist.

title: Alai
subTitle: Aathi and Meera go from constant clashes to discovering an unexpected bond while helping their friend pursue love during a journey away from home.

title: Bhakthi Neram
subTitle: Bhakthi Neram

title: Thiruda Thirudi
subTitle: Vasu, a youngster, is considered irresponsible by the woman he loves and his family. In order to gain their approval, he decides to mend his ways and prove his worth.

title: Maaveeran
subTitle: A rude princess acts arrogantly towards everyone around her. However, when she meets a simple village boy, she falls in love with him and changes her view towards life.

title: Budget Padmanabhan
subTitle: Padmanabhan, known as Budget for his miserly ways, faces a dilemma when his spendthrift wife hinders his efforts to save his father's house from loan sharks.

title: May Madham
subTitle: Tired of her overbearing father, Sandhya runs away from home. She later falls in love with Eeshwar, a man to whom she loses all her money.

title: My Dear Marthandan
subTitle: Wealthy village heir Marthandan grows weary of opulence and yearns for change. Soon, he embarks on a journey to embrace simplicity amidst urban poverty.

title: Annamalai
subTitle: Annamalai, a milkman, and Ashok, the son of a rich businessman, are childhood friends. However Ashok's father disapproves of their friendship and attempts to create a rift between the two.

title: Mettukudi
subTitle: A man pretends to be the son of a long-lost royal family to steal a precious sword. However, his plan runs into complications when the granddaughter of the sword's guardian falls in love with him.

title: Mettukudi
subTitle: A man pretends to be the son of a long-lost royal family to steal a precious sword. However, his plan runs into complications when the granddaughter of the sword's guardian falls in love with him.

title: Sangamam
subTitle: Selvam, a rural folk artist, falls in love with Abhirami, a classical dancer. However, things become complicated when her father disapproves of their relationship.

title: Rajadhi Raja
subTitle: Raja, a rich estate owner's son, comes back from abroad in order to avenge his dead father. However, things get complicated when he is framed, and he finds his doppelganger in his village.

title: Bhakthi Neram
subTitle: Bhakthi Neram

title: Johnny
subTitle: Johnny loves Archana, a singer, but their lives are disrupted when Johnny's lookalike kills his lover for infidelity and tries to pin the blame on Johnny. He also takes refuge in Archana's house.

title: Aalukkoru Aasai
subTitle: Arivazhagan plans on leading a happy life by choosing an independent educated girl as his partner. However, his orthodox grandparents trick him into marrying an illiterate woman.

title: Gajendra
subTitle: Gajendra, an orphan, unabashedly dotes on a girl with a mental disability. However, he faces trouble when his family questions his relationship with the girl, and he refuses to reveal the truth.

title: Kadhal Parisu
subTitle: A woman (Radha) falls in love with the man who saved her life.

title: ABCD
subTitle: Avi and Bhasha are two brothers who enjoy a lavish lifestyle and are later tricked by the former's father into living a life in poverty.

title: Vaanathaipola
subTitle: An older brother dedicates himself to his three younger brothers' success. As a result, he puts their needs first, making personal sacrifices to provide opportunities and support.

title: Ullathai Allitha
subTitle: Tired of his father's disciplinarian ways and to avoid marrying a girl chosen by the latter, Raja runs away to Ooty. There, he is hired as a driver by the man whose daughter he was supposed to marry.

title: Ullathai Allitha
subTitle: Tired of his father's disciplinarian ways and to avoid marrying a girl chosen by the latter, Raja runs away to Ooty. There, he is hired as a driver by the man whose daughter he was supposed to marry.

title: April Maadhathil
subTitle: Kathir, a poor young man, and Shweta, a rich young girl, meet in college and fall in love. However, they are unable to confess their feelings to each other.

title: Pandiya Naadu
subTitle: Sivakumar, a young man, lives in a close-knitted family. When a criminal kills his brother, he and his father decide to take revenge but in their own separate ways.

title: Bhakthi Neram
subTitle: Bhakthi Neram

title: Mundhanai Mudichu
subTitle: Mischievous Parimalam, known for pranking her villagers, falls for a widowed teacher. When he proves unyielding about not marrying her, she pulls a trick and does everything to win him over.

title: Veera
subTitle: When Muthu returns to his village, he learns that the girl he liked is dead and thus, eventually marries his employer's daughter. However, his old flame returns from the dead, leading to chaos.

title: Sivappu Sooriyan
subTitle: Vijay, a merchant navy officer, returns home to meet his sister, Selvi, and her husband, Vishwanthan. However, he finds out that they are missing and sets out to search for them.

title: Priyamanavale
subTitle: Vijay gets married to Priya at his father's behest, but on the condition that at the end of the year he will get to decide whether he wants to continue their marriage or terminate it.

title: Udhaya
subTitle: Udhaya falls in love with Vasanthi, but realises that she is already engaged. Later, when he is wrongly framed for a crime, she strives to prove his innocence.

title: Saamy
subTitle: Aarusaamy, a police officer, accepts bribes from Perumal, a gangster, in order to maintain peace in his district. However, circumstances force him to go against Perumal.

title: Chinna Gounder
subTitle: The village head is a man who sticks to honesty while making judgements. However, when he falls prey to a conspiracy, he bravely fights to ensure that justice prevails in his village.
